author: ghudson
msg: Fix issue #2054 (--stop-on-copy sometimes doesn't work in FSFS) and a
related class of bugs.  When we're looking for the most recent copy
target relevant to a path, we need to prefer child copy targets to
parent copy targets within the same revision.  If we take the parent
copy, it may not be relevant to the history of the child.
child targets to parent targets within a revision.
